1
00:00:01,084 --> 00:00:02,544
- [pensive music playing]
- [Marcus] <i>I need to talk to you.</i>

2
00:00:02,627 --> 00:00:04,713
<i>Why would you point to Datu Rahman?</i>

3
00:00:04,796 --> 00:00:07,882
<i>What do you know?</i>
<i>What's your role in the conspiracy?</i>

4
00:00:07,966 --> 00:00:08,925
What happened here?

5
00:00:09,009 --> 00:00:10,885
[paramedi] <i>Colonel Del Mundo</i>
<i>committed suicide.</i>

6
00:00:10,969 --> 00:00:14,180
[Marcus] <i>He's the one who prepared</i>
<i>the data and intel on Datu Rahman.</i>

7
00:00:14,264 --> 00:00:15,557
This is not suicide, sir.

8
00:00:15,640 --> 00:00:18,059
Reyes, what are you on about once again?!

9
00:00:18,143 --> 00:00:19,686
[Marcus] <i>They're cleaning everything up!</i>

10
00:00:19,769 --> 00:00:22,939
<i>This is the doing of the person</i>
<i>who's sabotaging our operations!</i>

11
00:00:23,982 --> 00:00:25,984
The person sent
by the Muslim Affairs has arrived.

12
00:00:26,568 --> 00:00:28,695
[Felix] <i>Already investigating</i>
<i>on what happened on the island.</i>

13
00:00:28,778 --> 00:00:29,738
<i>Don't you worry.</i>

14
00:00:29,821 --> 00:00:31,990
<i>Before he could find out the truth…</i>

15
00:00:34,284 --> 00:00:37,245
Jalil, there's a video
of Father circulating.

16
00:00:37,328 --> 00:00:38,997
[Jalil] <i>I'm looking into that right now.</i>

17
00:00:39,080 --> 00:00:40,206
[Omar] <i>What are you planning?</i>

18
00:00:40,290 --> 00:00:42,041
[Jalil] <i>I can't tell you.</i>

19
00:00:42,125 --> 00:00:43,793
What are you doing here?

20
00:00:43,877 --> 00:00:45,503
You have no right to go through that.

21
00:00:45,587 --> 00:00:46,629
I have the password.

22
00:00:46,713 --> 00:00:48,173
Are you doing this on purpose?

23
00:00:48,256 --> 00:00:49,841
[Azuelo] I granted him an authorization

24
00:00:49,924 --> 00:00:52,177
to review all those files.

25
00:00:52,260 --> 00:00:53,720
[Jalil] Sir, I'll review it later.

26
00:00:53,803 --> 00:00:55,555
After our meeting.

27
00:00:55,638 --> 00:00:57,348
We're the ones who have a meeting!

28
00:00:57,432 --> 00:01:01,311
[Jalil] <i>On selecting the new members</i>
<i>of Task Force Alpha,</i>

29
00:01:01,394 --> 00:01:02,395
<i>I'm a part of it.</i>

30
00:01:02,479 --> 00:01:05,774
I want to talk with them
before they can join Task Force Alpha.

31
00:01:05,857 --> 00:01:07,275
I selected them personally.

32
00:01:07,358 --> 00:01:10,070
[Jalil] <i>I just want to make sure</i>
<i>that the new members</i>

33
00:01:10,153 --> 00:01:12,280
<i>won't be like their predecessors.</i>

34
00:01:12,363 --> 00:01:13,364
- What did you just say?
- Marcus, enough!

35
00:01:13,448 --> 00:01:14,491
[Azuelo] Reyes!

36
00:01:15,075 --> 00:01:16,659
[in English] Who do you think you are?!

37
00:01:16,743 --> 00:01:19,120
Don't disrespect our comrades who died!

38
00:01:19,204 --> 00:01:21,331
What about those who died on the island?!

39
00:01:21,414 --> 00:01:25,126
<i>Innocent children and children</i>
<i>who left their parents too soon.</i>

40
00:01:25,210 --> 00:01:28,296
Who will apologize to them?

41
00:01:28,379 --> 00:01:29,339
You?!

42
00:01:34,177 --> 00:01:36,721
[mysterious theme music playing]

43
00:01:51,653 --> 00:01:53,655
[Manuel, in English] Ahmad,
thanks for coming.

44
00:01:53,738 --> 00:01:55,240
[in English] Thanks for listening.

45
00:01:55,824 --> 00:01:57,367
Santos, hey.

46
00:01:57,951 --> 00:02:01,037
[in English] Those are
very valuable insights, General Carillo.

47
00:02:01,121 --> 00:02:02,914
[in English] Thank you. Much honored, sir.

48
00:02:05,375 --> 00:02:07,293
- [Ahmad] Manuel!
- Oh, Ahmad!

49
00:02:07,377 --> 00:02:10,630
The President is pleased
with your recommendations.

50
00:02:10,713 --> 00:02:11,965
- [chuckles]
- [pensive music playing]

51
00:02:12,048 --> 00:02:14,592
It is without a doubt a huge help.

52
00:02:15,093 --> 00:02:16,761
- Thank you very much.
- [Manuel laughs]

53
00:02:16,845 --> 00:02:18,763
You're always welcome, Ahmad. [inhales]

54
00:02:18,847 --> 00:02:22,892
Ah… I'm always… happy
to be of service to the Republic.

55
00:02:22,976 --> 00:02:24,227
Mm-hmm.

56
00:02:24,310 --> 00:02:26,062
- [pats]
- [giggles]

57
00:02:26,604 --> 00:02:27,730
[Manuel exhales]

58
00:02:28,356 --> 00:02:29,774
What's next on the schedule?

59
00:02:30,358 --> 00:02:34,445
[grim music playing]

60
00:02:34,529 --> 00:02:36,531
[sighs heavily, mutters]

61
00:02:36,614 --> 00:02:39,617
- Ma, are you alright?
- [shushing]

62
00:02:39,701 --> 00:02:42,036
- You got shoved?
- [coughs] I'm alright, son.

63
00:02:42,120 --> 00:02:45,832
Our nurse, Jamilah, lent me a hand anyway.

64
00:02:46,332 --> 00:02:47,542
Jamilah!

65
00:02:48,042 --> 00:02:50,503
- Doc.
- [Teresa] This is my son, Marcus.

66
00:02:50,587 --> 00:02:52,755
[morose music playing]

67
00:03:10,773 --> 00:03:11,983
Thank you, Jamilah.

68
00:03:14,110 --> 00:03:15,612
I heard you helped my mother.

69
00:03:16,905 --> 00:03:17,739
[Jamilah breathes heavily]

70
00:03:17,822 --> 00:03:20,241
[Teresa] <i>I won't judge your father.</i>

71
00:03:20,909 --> 00:03:22,452
But I'm begging you.

72
00:03:22,952 --> 00:03:26,414
I hope you also don't label
my son as a murderer,

73
00:03:26,497 --> 00:03:28,416
because he is not a bad person.

74
00:03:28,499 --> 00:03:32,462
[morose music continues]

75
00:03:50,271 --> 00:03:54,651
[morose music continues, ends]

76
00:03:55,526 --> 00:03:57,195
[sighs in frustration]

77
00:03:57,278 --> 00:03:59,280
- [breathes deeply]
- [gloomy music playing]

78
00:03:59,364 --> 00:04:01,908
- [Jalil] <i>You're hurting?</i>
- [Lara, in English] <i>Yes! Yes!</i>

79
00:04:01,991 --> 00:04:03,952
[Jalil] Those who died on the island,

80
00:04:04,035 --> 00:04:06,537
they also had friends, Agent Angeles.

81
00:04:12,210 --> 00:04:14,003
[wailing]

82
00:04:18,258 --> 00:04:22,929
[stirring music playing]

83
00:04:28,142 --> 00:04:30,186
[digital trilling]

84
00:04:44,367 --> 00:04:45,868
[muttering] Everything's been deleted…

85
00:04:47,120 --> 00:04:48,830
[stirring music continues]

86
00:05:10,810 --> 00:05:12,687
[Jalil] Why were all of you murdered?

87
00:05:20,778 --> 00:05:23,281
You have nothing to worry about, Boss.

88
00:05:23,364 --> 00:05:26,034
I already cleaned up all the loose ends.

89
00:05:26,117 --> 00:05:28,953
As well as those we ordered
to delete some files.

90
00:05:29,787 --> 00:05:31,080
I've shut them all up.

91
00:05:32,081 --> 00:05:34,167
Espino has nothing to sniff out now.

92
00:05:36,794 --> 00:05:38,004
[in English] We need to talk.

93
00:05:39,839 --> 00:05:42,467
[suspenseful sting]

94
00:05:42,550 --> 00:05:44,719
Why do they have to die, Dad?

95
00:05:45,219 --> 00:05:46,888
Why did they die?!

96
00:05:46,971 --> 00:05:48,848
[suspenseful sting]

97
00:05:57,565 --> 00:06:00,234
Oliver, Patrick, Russel, and even Harold.

98
00:06:01,027 --> 00:06:02,612
The civilians on the island.

99
00:06:02,695 --> 00:06:05,615
All those innocent people,
why did they have to die?!

100
00:06:07,825 --> 00:06:10,119
[in English] Dad, look at me! Answer me!

101
00:06:10,203 --> 00:06:12,622
Why did they all have to die?!

102
00:06:12,705 --> 00:06:15,416
[in English] Was it really necessary?!
Huh?!

103
00:06:15,500 --> 00:06:16,876
- Lara.
- [Lara huffs]

104
00:06:16,959 --> 00:06:19,212
You could've gone ahead with your plans.

105
00:06:19,712 --> 00:06:21,547
[in English] Why did you have
to massacre those people?!

106
00:06:21,631 --> 00:06:23,174
Lara!

107
00:06:23,257 --> 00:06:25,551
[tense music intensifies]

108
00:06:25,635 --> 00:06:29,472
Don't you get it yet?

109
00:06:29,555 --> 00:06:33,476
How many times
do I have to explain it to you?

110
00:06:34,102 --> 00:06:38,981
You know damn well
why they needed to be silenced.

111
00:06:42,819 --> 00:06:44,278
[Lara, in English] What the hell
is happening?

112
00:06:44,362 --> 00:06:46,447
[in English] Fix my visuals!
Where are my visuals?!

113
00:06:46,531 --> 00:06:47,949
[in English] The mission is compromised.

114
00:06:48,032 --> 00:06:49,992
[Marcus, in English] <i>I repeat,</i>
<i>the mission is compromised.</i>

115
00:06:50,076 --> 00:06:51,202
[headphones clatter]

116
00:06:52,328 --> 00:06:53,454
[breathing heavily]

117
00:06:53,538 --> 00:06:54,914
[Marcus] <i>Who gave the order?</i>

118
00:06:54,997 --> 00:06:57,291
- [Lara] <i>Which order?</i>
- [Marcus] To neutralize the village!

119
00:06:57,375 --> 00:06:58,835
Who gave that order?

120
00:06:58,918 --> 00:07:00,711
Marcus, no one gave such an order.

121
00:07:00,795 --> 00:07:02,672
[in English] I was monitoring
the operation the whole time.

122
00:07:02,755 --> 00:07:03,756
- I didn't--
- Lara, there was an order!

123
00:07:03,840 --> 00:07:05,216
- No one gave such an order.
- Someone--

124
00:07:05,299 --> 00:07:07,009
- Someone did, Lara!
- Agent Reyes.

125
00:07:08,928 --> 00:07:11,222
[Lara] Dad. Dad, what happened?

126
00:07:11,722 --> 00:07:13,391
Why were our comms hijacked?

127
00:07:13,474 --> 00:07:14,976
[in English] I thought it was going
to be a peaceful arrest.

128
00:07:15,059 --> 00:07:18,729
- [in English] What happened?
- I said it was going to be an arrest.

129
00:07:19,814 --> 00:07:21,858
[in English] I never said
it was going to be peaceful.

130
00:07:23,317 --> 00:07:27,613
Besides, I don't have to tell you

131
00:07:27,697 --> 00:07:30,616
everything I need to do, Lara.

132
00:07:30,700 --> 00:07:33,369
[in English] I-I know that,
but those people, they were…

133
00:07:33,453 --> 00:07:34,662
[in English] Casualties.

134
00:07:38,749 --> 00:07:42,003
[in English] Keep your eye
on the prize, Lara.

135
00:07:42,587 --> 00:07:45,047
[in English] This is all
for the greater good.

136
00:07:48,384 --> 00:07:49,510
My dear.

137
00:07:50,470 --> 00:07:51,387
[grim music playing]

138
00:07:51,471 --> 00:07:55,641
If you want to make our dreams a reality,

139
00:07:55,725 --> 00:07:57,477
you need to learn to accept

140
00:07:58,060 --> 00:08:02,315
that there are going to be casualties.

141
00:08:04,233 --> 00:08:06,736
It's hard, it's painful.

142
00:08:06,819 --> 00:08:11,908
[in English] But it's a choice
we have to make.

143
00:08:14,535 --> 00:08:17,413
All footage was wiped.

144
00:08:17,997 --> 00:08:21,792
Whoever hijacked our comms
must've done this too.

145
00:08:21,876 --> 00:08:26,005
But how did they erase all of the files?
Who is sabotaging us, and why?

146
00:08:28,799 --> 00:08:30,343
[Lara] <i>How could you do that?</i>

147
00:08:31,177 --> 00:08:33,763
<i>How could you kill them?</i>
<i>They were our friends!</i>

148
00:08:33,846 --> 00:08:35,598
How could you kill our friends?!

149
00:08:36,349 --> 00:08:37,350
Lara.

150
00:08:39,352 --> 00:08:42,605
Yes, they were our friends, but…

151
00:08:43,189 --> 00:08:45,733
I had to carry out the General's order.

152
00:08:45,816 --> 00:08:46,817
Do you understand that?

153
00:08:48,694 --> 00:08:52,031
[Manuel] I know. That's why…

154
00:08:53,324 --> 00:08:58,454
you shouldn't have left loose ends.

155
00:08:59,330 --> 00:09:02,083
[in English] But you failed.

156
00:09:02,166 --> 00:09:04,585
[in English] So I had to do something.

157
00:09:04,669 --> 00:09:09,382
I had to clean up your mess.

158
00:09:10,383 --> 00:09:17,014
Otherwise, they would've gotten
in the way of our plans.

159
00:09:17,098 --> 00:09:20,768
[grim music continues]

160
00:09:21,477 --> 00:09:22,395
[in English] No.

161
00:09:23,980 --> 00:09:24,981
Lara.

162
00:09:26,691 --> 00:09:28,818
Lara, what is going on with you?

163
00:09:30,236 --> 00:09:32,405
You used to be brave.

164
00:09:32,947 --> 00:09:35,908
You were fighting for something.

165
00:09:36,784 --> 00:09:43,499
But you've become so weak.
[in English] Emotional.

166
00:09:43,583 --> 00:09:44,417
[exhales]

167
00:09:44,500 --> 00:09:50,131
[in English] You used to make me so proud.

168
00:09:50,631 --> 00:09:51,465
Lara…

169
00:09:52,633 --> 00:09:57,221
Where is the girl I raised?

170
00:09:58,848 --> 00:10:00,766
[grunts] I know it hurts.

171
00:10:01,767 --> 00:10:05,813
Lives were lost.

172
00:10:06,564 --> 00:10:10,026
But you can't let

173
00:10:10,109 --> 00:10:13,279
- [Lara sobs]
- what happened to your parents

174
00:10:13,362 --> 00:10:16,616
happen again.

175
00:10:16,699 --> 00:10:20,703
[grim music continues]

176
00:10:20,786 --> 00:10:23,372
But it ended up
working in your favor, correct?

177
00:10:26,208 --> 00:10:28,836
You caught Datu Rahman.

178
00:10:29,337 --> 00:10:35,926
However, he escaped
while he was under your custody.

179
00:10:37,928 --> 00:10:41,390
And who's to blame for that, Lara?

180
00:10:42,391 --> 00:10:43,434
[weakly] Me.

181
00:10:44,310 --> 00:10:46,687
I can't hear you!

182
00:10:46,771 --> 00:10:49,273
[crying] Me. It's my fault.

183
00:10:49,815 --> 00:10:51,400
[Lara sobs]

184
00:10:52,109 --> 00:10:57,907
We all have a role to play in this war.

185
00:10:58,574 --> 00:11:02,787
Let me do my part.

186
00:11:03,663 --> 00:11:07,458
And you focus on doing yours.

187
00:11:08,501 --> 00:11:10,336
Are we clear?

188
00:11:10,419 --> 00:11:17,301
[grim music continues]

189
00:11:24,517 --> 00:11:25,559
- [Lara sniffles]
- [tongue clicks]

190
00:11:25,643 --> 00:11:30,439
[in English] And stop disappointing me.

191
00:11:30,940 --> 00:11:33,359
[breath quivers, sniffles]

192
00:11:34,652 --> 00:11:35,653
[Manuel sighs]

193
00:11:37,696 --> 00:11:38,948
[sniffles]

194
00:11:40,533 --> 00:11:42,243
- Enough with the tears.
- [Lara sobs]

195
00:11:42,326 --> 00:11:43,619
[Manuel] That's enough.

196
00:11:45,454 --> 00:11:47,456
[Manuel] Stop crying, Lara.

197
00:11:49,291 --> 00:11:51,127
[sobbing continues]

198
00:11:54,422 --> 00:11:57,049
[morose music playing]

199
00:11:57,133 --> 00:11:58,384
[sighs]

200
00:12:00,594 --> 00:12:01,595
[Lara exhales heavily]

201
00:12:11,730 --> 00:12:13,190
[Felix] You alright, madam?

202
00:12:22,867 --> 00:12:25,286
You know, the General's right.

203
00:12:27,538 --> 00:12:29,331
We don't see it yet.

204
00:12:29,999 --> 00:12:33,377
But in the end, he's always right.

205
00:12:35,171 --> 00:12:36,422
[softly] Right?

206
00:12:40,092 --> 00:12:41,343
- [loud thwacks]
- [groans]

207
00:12:41,427 --> 00:12:42,845
[Lara whimpers]

208
00:12:42,928 --> 00:12:44,138
- [screams]
- Lara, hang on--

209
00:12:44,221 --> 00:12:45,431
[Lara grunts]

210
00:12:45,514 --> 00:12:48,976
[grunting, screaming]

211
00:12:52,229 --> 00:12:57,651
[tense music playing]

212
00:13:10,581 --> 00:13:11,707
Ma.

213
00:13:14,710 --> 00:13:16,587
About Jamilah…

214
00:13:17,254 --> 00:13:18,506
Why, son?

215
00:13:20,508 --> 00:13:22,176
Is she mad at me?

216
00:13:22,259 --> 00:13:23,302
[morose music playing]

217
00:13:23,385 --> 00:13:24,845
[Teresa] <i>I'm begging you.</i>

218
00:13:26,013 --> 00:13:30,017
Please don't think of my son
as a murderer.

219
00:13:30,100 --> 00:13:32,353
[Teresa] <i>Because he's not a bad person.</i>

220
00:13:33,896 --> 00:13:35,564
Why'd you ask?

221
00:13:36,398 --> 00:13:38,067
[sighs]

222
00:13:38,734 --> 00:13:41,779
You know. I'm not exactly liked
by a lot of people right now.

223
00:13:42,863 --> 00:13:44,365
Especially the Muslims.

224
00:13:44,907 --> 00:13:46,742
Because of what happened on the island.

225
00:13:46,825 --> 00:13:48,160
[morose music continues]

226
00:13:48,244 --> 00:13:50,120
Son.

227
00:13:50,204 --> 00:13:52,873
How many times do I have to tell you

228
00:13:53,624 --> 00:13:56,001
that what happened wasn't your fault?

229
00:13:57,086 --> 00:13:58,879
Whether it was my fault or not,

230
00:14:01,423 --> 00:14:03,217
many people still died.

231
00:14:05,719 --> 00:14:09,515
That's what some jerk at the office
keeps rubbing in my face.

232
00:14:10,015 --> 00:14:12,184
Don't let them get to you.

233
00:14:12,768 --> 00:14:14,478
They're just looking for trouble.

234
00:14:14,562 --> 00:14:17,565
[music swelling]

235
00:14:17,648 --> 00:14:19,191
[inhales, exhales deeply]

236
00:14:19,275 --> 00:14:20,818
But, Ma… [sighs]

237
00:14:21,569 --> 00:14:24,154
I still carry the weight
of their anger and grief.

238
00:14:24,238 --> 00:14:27,032
[somber music playing]

239
00:14:27,116 --> 00:14:29,076
No matter what I do,

240
00:14:30,411 --> 00:14:32,746
I can't bring back the lives
that were lost.

241
00:14:36,000 --> 00:14:39,670
[sighing]

242
00:14:55,019 --> 00:14:57,813
[stirring music playing]

243
00:15:21,962 --> 00:15:24,048
They erased all the evidence

244
00:15:25,549 --> 00:15:28,135
and silenced the people involved.

245
00:15:28,218 --> 00:15:32,723
[pensive music playing]

246
00:15:36,226 --> 00:15:40,272
COL. LUIS DEL MUNDO FOUND DEAD

247
00:15:43,484 --> 00:15:45,736
[Jalil] <i>The more I learn,</i>

248
00:15:46,236 --> 00:15:48,530
<i>the more questions I have.</i>

249
00:15:49,031 --> 00:15:51,450
<i>But I know I'm on the right track.</i>

250
00:15:53,661 --> 00:15:55,537
<i>I can save you, Father,</i>

251
00:15:56,372 --> 00:15:59,833
<i>and I'll find out</i>
<i>who masterminded everything.</i>

252
00:15:59,917 --> 00:16:02,920
[music swelling]

253
00:16:03,003 --> 00:16:04,505
[music fades]

254
00:16:06,465 --> 00:16:08,092
[frustrated scream]

255
00:16:08,175 --> 00:16:10,052
[exhales heavily]

256
00:16:10,135 --> 00:16:17,101
- [crying quietly]
- [melancholic music playing]

257
00:16:21,939 --> 00:16:25,067
[breathing heavily]

258
00:16:26,735 --> 00:16:29,321
[chuckles bitterly]

259
00:16:33,909 --> 00:16:35,953
[Lara's mother]
<i>Just stay here and play, okay?</i>

260
00:16:36,036 --> 00:16:37,037
Mommy needs to work. Be good.

261
00:16:37,621 --> 00:16:39,581
Okay, Mommy! Do your best!

262
00:16:40,916 --> 00:16:42,793
Don't tire yourselves out with Daddy!

263
00:16:42,876 --> 00:16:44,420
- [mother chuckles]
- Bye-bye!

264
00:16:44,503 --> 00:16:45,337
[indistinct chatter]

265
00:16:45,421 --> 00:16:50,259
[melancholic music continues]

266
00:16:50,342 --> 00:16:53,012
- [mother] Captain.
- [captain] Doctor.

267
00:16:53,095 --> 00:16:55,514
Thank you so much
for coming back to our town.

268
00:16:55,597 --> 00:16:58,434
Sorry, my husband and I took
a while to return.

269
00:16:58,517 --> 00:17:01,937
- Are there many patients now?
- Yes, they're all here.

270
00:17:02,021 --> 00:17:03,772
- Thank you.
- No problem.

271
00:17:04,648 --> 00:17:07,234
[sinister music playing]

272
00:17:08,318 --> 00:17:10,070
- [explosion]
- [shrieks]

273
00:17:10,154 --> 00:17:11,321
- [people clamoring]
- [gunshots]

274
00:17:11,405 --> 00:17:13,574
- [explosion]
- [woman 1 crying]

275
00:17:13,657 --> 00:17:16,535
[young Lara crying]

276
00:17:16,618 --> 00:17:19,288
- [body thuds]
- [woman 2 screaming]

277
00:17:25,085 --> 00:17:28,797
[young Lara] Mommy! Daddy!

278
00:17:29,506 --> 00:17:32,217
[dramatic music playing]

279
00:17:32,301 --> 00:17:34,470
What did you do?!

280
00:17:41,602 --> 00:17:43,437
[young Lara sobs] <i>Mommy!</i>

281
00:17:44,646 --> 00:17:46,065
<i>Mommy!</i>

282
00:17:46,565 --> 00:17:49,526
<i>Mommy, Daddy! Mommy!</i>

283
00:17:53,614 --> 00:17:54,823
[young Lara sobbing]

284
00:17:54,907 --> 00:17:56,658
- [man 1] Come with me!
- What are you doing?!

285
00:17:56,742 --> 00:17:57,743
Let me go!

286
00:17:57,826 --> 00:18:00,204
- Stop resisting! Just come with me!
- No!

287
00:18:00,913 --> 00:18:01,997
[man 1] <i>If you don't want to end up</i>
<i>like them, come along!</i>

288
00:18:02,081 --> 00:18:03,457
[young Lara] <i>Mommy! Daddy!</i>

289
00:18:03,540 --> 00:18:06,251
- <i>Mommy! Mommy!</i>
- <i>Come on!</i>

290
00:18:10,798 --> 00:18:12,007
[sobbing]

291
00:18:12,091 --> 00:18:14,176
- [children sob]
- [man 2] Hurry up. Get inside!

292
00:18:14,259 --> 00:18:15,761
- [child] Stop!
- [man] Faster!

293
00:18:15,844 --> 00:18:16,678
[man] Stand over there!

294
00:18:16,762 --> 00:18:21,350
- [children crying]
- [indistinct shouting]

295
00:18:21,433 --> 00:18:22,351
[man] Quiet!

296
00:18:22,851 --> 00:18:25,354
Stop crying, all of you!

297
00:18:25,896 --> 00:18:27,898
The buyers will come for you!

298
00:18:27,981 --> 00:18:30,275
[children sobbing]

299
00:18:30,359 --> 00:18:34,404
Those who behave will be taken
to the sardines factory…

300
00:18:35,447 --> 00:18:38,367
to work! But the troublemakers?

301
00:18:38,450 --> 00:18:39,451
[man chuckles dryly]

302
00:18:39,535 --> 00:18:41,328
They're in big trouble!

303
00:18:41,411 --> 00:18:43,288
- You monsters!
- [man 1] What?

304
00:18:43,372 --> 00:18:44,832
- [man 2] Stop it!
- [man 1 shouts] You're brave, huh?

305
00:18:44,915 --> 00:18:46,041
- You've got some nerve!
- [young Lara] Let me go!

306
00:18:46,125 --> 00:18:48,544
- [man 3 grunts] Stay there.
- [man 1] Someone hold her!

307
00:18:48,627 --> 00:18:50,879
- [man 1] Hold her down!
- [young Lara sobs]

308
00:18:50,963 --> 00:18:55,008
- [crying] What will you do to me?!
- [man 2] Just follow!

309
00:18:55,092 --> 00:18:56,844
- [young Lara screaming, crying]
- [man 2] What now?

310
00:18:56,927 --> 00:19:00,055
Please! Don't do this to me!

311
00:19:00,139 --> 00:19:03,559
[man 1] This is what happens
if you don't listen!

312
00:19:03,642 --> 00:19:05,936
[crying]

313
00:19:06,854 --> 00:19:10,274
[grim music playing]

314
00:19:11,608 --> 00:19:13,777
[crying]

315
00:19:31,587 --> 00:19:38,177
[crying]

316
00:19:47,728 --> 00:19:50,981
[grim music continues]

317
00:20:05,579 --> 00:20:07,789
[suspenseful music playing]

318
00:20:36,735 --> 00:20:39,279
You again?
You're really stubborn, aren't you?

319
00:20:39,363 --> 00:20:41,073
Where are you going, huh?!

320
00:20:41,156 --> 00:20:42,783
Let's see if you're brave now!

321
00:20:42,866 --> 00:20:45,369
- [young Lara grunts] Argh!
- [man groans] That hurts!

322
00:20:46,870 --> 00:20:49,081
That's enough! I said, enough!

323
00:20:49,164 --> 00:20:50,791
Do you want me to kill you?!

324
00:20:52,251 --> 00:20:54,753
[tense music playing]

325
00:21:01,093 --> 00:21:02,803
- [gunshots]
- [grunts] <i>Argh!</i>

326
00:21:03,595 --> 00:21:05,514
- [body thuds]
- [children clamoring]

327
00:21:05,597 --> 00:21:07,808
[crying]

328
00:21:10,811 --> 00:21:13,647
[police] <i>Nobody move!</i>

329
00:21:16,233 --> 00:21:17,651
[police] Somebody grab the gun!

330
00:21:18,193 --> 00:21:19,695
[shudders]

331
00:21:20,779 --> 00:21:23,115
- [indistint chattering]
- Are you okay?

332
00:21:23,198 --> 00:21:24,574
Were you hurt?

333
00:21:26,702 --> 00:21:27,911
What's your name?

334
00:21:28,829 --> 00:21:30,622
L-Lara…

335
00:21:31,123 --> 00:21:33,417
Lara Angeles.

336
00:21:33,500 --> 00:21:35,669
[sniffles]

337
00:21:40,090 --> 00:21:42,718
My name is Major Manuel Carillo.

338
00:21:43,343 --> 00:21:44,678
Don't worry, Lara.

339
00:21:46,388 --> 00:21:47,597
I'll take care of you.

340
00:21:48,640 --> 00:21:52,102
[melancholic music playing]

341
00:22:04,489 --> 00:22:05,574
[Manuel] <i>That…</i>

342
00:22:06,074 --> 00:22:08,327
<i>is Datu Rahman Abubakar.</i>

343
00:22:08,410 --> 00:22:10,329
<i>He killed your parents.</i>

344
00:22:10,412 --> 00:22:17,002
[somber music playing]

345
00:22:17,085 --> 00:22:19,046
And that island right there…

346
00:22:20,088 --> 00:22:21,631
That's where he's hiding.

347
00:22:27,888 --> 00:22:31,558
[Manuel] <i>Stop disappointing me.</i>

348
00:22:39,024 --> 00:22:42,486
[melancholic music playing]

349
00:22:46,573 --> 00:22:50,702
[Manuel] I know that you like Lara.

350
00:22:51,912 --> 00:22:53,246
[Felix] Boss.

351
00:22:55,540 --> 00:22:56,625
[Lara] Here.

352
00:22:58,794 --> 00:22:59,878
[in English] Thank you.

353
00:23:01,963 --> 00:23:05,342
That's why… I'm counting on you…

354
00:23:06,676 --> 00:23:09,346
to take care of her.

355
00:23:09,930 --> 00:23:12,224
Keep an eye on her.

356
00:23:13,058 --> 00:23:14,893
I love Lara very much.

357
00:23:16,353 --> 00:23:20,982
That's why… I don't want her to get hurt.

358
00:23:21,650 --> 00:23:23,485
As soon as…

359
00:23:23,568 --> 00:23:25,904
she gets in the way…

360
00:23:26,530 --> 00:23:28,740
of our plan…

361
00:23:28,824 --> 00:23:30,158
[suspenseful music playing]

362
00:23:52,013 --> 00:23:54,558
[suspenseful music playing]

363
00:23:58,228 --> 00:23:59,604
[man] <i>There's a shootout between</i>
<i>our police and some robbers</i>

364
00:23:59,688 --> 00:24:01,106
<i>at Central Heritage Bank.</i>

365
00:24:01,189 --> 00:24:04,985
[reporter] <i>…which is currently being</i>
<i>held up by the notorious gang, Metal 13.</i>

366
00:24:05,068 --> 00:24:07,487
The criminals are carrying
high-powered firearms.

367
00:24:07,571 --> 00:24:10,073
I don't want any casualties
on your very first day.

368
00:24:10,157 --> 00:24:11,616
[officers, in English] Yes, sir!

369
00:24:11,700 --> 00:24:14,452
[in English] Alpha One, this is Base.
We have a visual on the target.

370
00:24:14,536 --> 00:24:15,704
[Lara, in English] <i>Black van heading east.</i>

371
00:24:20,709 --> 00:24:23,086
- [overlapping chatter]
- [Teresa] What's going on?

372
00:24:23,170 --> 00:24:26,715
Marcus, they're heading towards S…
towards S. Trinidad Hospital.

373
00:24:29,217 --> 00:24:31,261
What's in S. Trinidad Hospital?

374
00:24:31,344 --> 00:24:32,679
Marcus' mom is a doctor at that hospital.

375
00:24:34,347 --> 00:24:36,558
- [man] Nobody move!
- [screaming]

376
00:24:36,641 --> 00:24:38,935
Nobody move!

377
00:24:40,145 --> 00:24:42,147
I'm going to kill them all!
